Data Access Object (DAO) is an object that provides an abstract interface to some type of * database or other persistence mechanism. By mapping application calls to the persistence layer, * DAO provide some specific data operations without exposing details of the database. This * isolation supports the Single responsibility principle. It separates what data accesses the * application needs, in terms of domain-specific objects and data types (the public interface of * the DAO), from how these needs can be satisfied with a specific DBMS. * *
